result.name: Hyatt Regency Hong Kong, Sha Tin

reviews.text: Got a free upgrade to a family suite. Amazing view from the room, great fitness centre and a huge swimming pool. Hotel staff was helpful with everything. There's a seven eleven very close to the hotel if you want to buy anything. The hotel has a very attractive bar next to the swimming pool. The suite was huge and included a microwave two baths and three washrooms.
Clean room.. Very good Location... Mountain or Sea View... Excellent Staff.. Always ready to help.  Good Vegetarian food choices also.

Perfect hotel with perfect service. Little bit far from everything but if u want to chill I peaceful place in Hong Kong it's good place. It's situated near to beach, but it's difficult to get there.
Breakfast and restaurants are pervect. Menu is huge even in room service. But the price is not so friendly.

The room was really big with a great view to the city and river. People are always friendly and the Hotel offers a lot like pool, fitness club and meeting rooms.
Negative was I expected it a bit more cleaner for a five star Hotel. Some corners and especially the floor got left out from cleaning.
Nice hotel with a fair rate. Good Chinese restaurant at the 4th floor. Rooms are clean and comfortable.

reviews.text: Booked this restaurant because of its location. During weekend, dinner duration was restricted to 2 hours only. The first round started 5.30pm. Service was OK but the food was far too expensive for what was offered in the plates. The roast duck came with three small dishes of skin and meat. Barely enough to be shared among a family of five. Additional charges applied for the lettuce wrap meat dish and soup. The sweet and sour pork was a bit fatty. The birthday lotus buns had a quarter of egg yolk as the filling. Not recommended for the cost charged.

A wonderful culinary experience.... exquisite ...wait till you try the amazing dessert: fermented tofu cheese cake, wuloong tea ice cream... went again and again delightful and enjoyable evening... must try the exotic dessert!!!
I had my lunch with my relatives on Sunday. You can find excellent dim sum and other Chinese dishes. Service is also good. A little pricy, but it is inside the hotel, so it is not unexpected.
Most Cantonese dishes are well prepared & tasty, prices not cheap but acceptable for a hotel outlet. Only drawback is the rather cramply placed tables.

Pleasant, atmosphere. Friendly staff. Excellent service. Advisable to book in advance if you'd like their duck and always advisable to book a table. Prices are a bit on the higher end as you would expect. Peking duck three course is what we always have. Along with the cha siu, and pan fried dumplings.

One critique would be their tea glasses. You would expect them to be of better quality in a place like this. On a few occasions the glasses were wonky.
